If you've just bought an electric car — or you're about to — one of the first things you'll need is a proper home charger. Plugging into a standard three-pin socket works, but it's slow, inefficient, and puts unnecessary strain on your home's wiring.

A dedicated home EV charger gives you faster, safer, and much smarter charging. And with the OZEV government grant covering up to £350 of installation costs, now is a great time to get one fitted.

We've spent weeks researching and comparing every major option available to UK buyers in 2026. Here are the seven best.

