The Ohme Home Pro is the smartest home charger on the UK market right now — and it's become our go-to recommendation for most buyers.

What sets it apart is its deep integration with smart electricity tariffs. If you're on Octopus Energy's Intelligent Octopus tariff (which many EV owners are), the Ohme will automatically charge your car when electricity prices are lowest — often in the early hours of the morning. Over a year, this can save you £200–£400 compared to charging at peak times.

The app is genuinely excellent: clean, intuitive, and packed with useful data. You can see exactly how much each charge costs, set schedules, track your carbon footprint, and monitor charging history. It also integrates with solar panels, so if you've got panels on your roof, the Ohme will prioritise using your free solar power before drawing from the grid.

Installation is straightforward for any OZEV-registered installer, and it qualifies for the government grant. The only downside? You do pay a premium — but for most people, the energy savings more than offset the extra cost within the first 12 months.

**Rating: ★★★★★ 4.9/5**

