If you have solar panels — or plan to get them — the Zappi is almost certainly the best choice for you. It's been purpose-built for renewable energy integration, and nothing else on the market comes close.

The Eco+ mode is the killer feature: the Zappi will only charge your car using surplus solar energy. So on a sunny day, you're essentially charging for free. In Eco mode, it tops up with grid power when solar isn't enough. And in Fast mode, it charges at full speed regardless of solar output.

If you don't have solar panels, there are probably smarter options at a similar price point. But for green-minded homeowners with renewables, the Zappi is the obvious choice.

