## What to Look for When Buying a Home EV Charger

### Charging Speed
For home use, a **7.4kW charger** is the sweet spot. It'll charge most EVs overnight from empty. You generally don't need faster than this at home — 22kW chargers are for commercial use and require three-phase power that most homes don't have.

### Smart Features
A smart charger lets you schedule charging for off-peak hours, which can save you significant money if you're on a smart tariff like Octopus Go. The Ohme Home Pro in particular can cut your overnight charging costs to as little as 7p/kWh.

### OZEV Grant Eligibility
The UK government's OZEV grant gives eligible homeowners **up to £350 off the cost of buying and installing a home charger**. All seven chargers on this list qualify. [See our full OZEV grant guide →](/guides/ev-charger-government-grant-uk/)

### Tethered vs Untethered
- **Tethered**: Cable permanently attached to the unit. More convenient — just plug in and go.
- **Untethered**: No cable — you use your own. More flexible if you might change cars, or have multiple cars with different connectors.

Most buyers prefer tethered for daily home use.

